      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Seat</th><th>Role</th><th>Key ID</th><th>State colours</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><span class="dp-badge navy">GOV</span></td><td>Governor</td><td>CBK-KEY-01</td><td rowspan="5">Grey = not yet voted · Green = approved · Red = rejected</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="dp-badge navy">DEP</span></td><td>Deputy Governor</td><td>CBK-KEY-02</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="dp-badge navy">RISK</span></td><td>Chief Risk Officer</td><td>CBK-KEY-03</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="dp-badge navy">COMP</span></td><td>Head of Compliance</td><td>CBK-KEY-04</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="dp-badge navy">EXT</span></td><td>External Auditor</td><td>CBK-KEY-EXT</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <p>
        <strong>Threshold trigger:</strong> as soon as <code>yes_votes / quorum_required ≥ 0.67</code>,
        the progress bar transitions from amber to green, the <strong>Approve</strong> button
        becomes active, and <code>GovernanceQuorum.threshold_met_at</code> is recorded.
      </p>

      <h3>Right Pane — Governance Controls &amp; Properties</h3>

      <h4>Quorum Status Bar</h4>
      <p>
        A styled <code>QProgressBar</code> (0–100) in the Properties tab. Colour driven
        by the approval ratio:
      </p>
      <div class="dp-rule">
        ratio ≥ 0.67 → green gradient  (#1b5e20 → #4caf50)<br>
        ratio ≥ 0.33 → amber gradient  (#e65100 → #ffb74d)<br>
        ratio &lt; 0.33 → red gradient    (#b71c1c → #ef5350)
      </div>

      <h4>Time-to-Expiry Label</h4>
      <p>Computed statically from <code>effective_date</code>:</p>
      <div class="dp-rule">
        days &lt; 0   → "EXPIRED (Nd ago)"   — red text<br>
        days = 0   → "Effective TODAY"       — green text<br>
        days = 1   → "1 day remaining"       — amber text<br>
        days &gt; 1  → "N days remaining"     — amber text<br>
        empty date → "—"                     — grey text
      </div>

      <h4>DLT Policy Anchoring — Immutable Seal Section</h4>
      <p>
        Located in the Properties tab. Populated by <code>GET /api/v2/dlt/status</code>
        on tab initialization and after every anchor operation.
      </p>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Widget</th><th>API source</th><th>Behaviour</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Node Status</td><td><code>data.node_status</code></td><td>Green = active · Amber = degraded · Red = offline</td></tr>
          <tr><td>⬡ IMMUTABLE SEAL badge</td><td>Static label</td><td>Active only if framework status ≠ SUSPENDED</td></tr>
          <tr><td>● Sync Status dot</td><td><code>data.sync_status</code> + <code>node_status</code></td><td>Green ● Synced (+ block #) if node active and synced; amber ◌ Syncing… otherwise</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Anchor Record hash</td><td><code>data.last_anchor_tx</code></td><td>Full hex hash displayed; ⧉ button copies to clipboard with 1.5 s ✓ feedback</td></tr>
          <tr><td>View Policy JSON</td><td>Cached proposal object</td><td>Toggles a dark code-pane showing indented JSON of <code>m_currentProposal</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Accrue Policy (Anchor)</td><td>POST /api/v2/governance/anchor</td><td>Hashes policy_json → sends to DLT → updates DLTAnchor record; refreshes DLT status</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>
    </div>

    <%# ── §4 UI Behavior ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── %>
    <div class="dp-section" id="ui-behavior">
      <div class="dp-section-header">
        <div class="dp-section-num">§4</div>
        <h2>UI Behavior Specifications</h2>
      </div>

      <h3>Approve Button — Distinct Visual &amp; Double-Auth</h3>
      <p>
        The <strong>🔒 Approve</strong> button is visually isolated from utility buttons
        (Search, Add Condition, Audit Trail) by a vertical line separator. It uses a
        distinct green style (<code>#1b5e20</code> background, white text, bold, 12 px font)
        so operators cannot accidentally trigger it during navigation.
      </p>
      <div class="dp-callout dp-warn">
        <span class="dp-ci">⚠</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Double-Auth for High-Risk proposals:</strong> when <code>risk_level = high</code>,
          clicking Approve opens a modal requiring the operator to (a) enter their authorisation
          PIN and (b) type the word <code>APPROVE</code> verbatim before the vote API call fires.
          Closing the dialog without completing both fields cancels the action silently.
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Right-Click Context Menus</h3>

      <h4>Active Policy Briefs Table</h4>
      <p>Right-clicking any row in <code>tblGovProposals</code> opens:</p>
      <div class="dp-context-menu">
        <div class="dp-context-item">View Full Audit Trail</div>
        <div class="dp-context-item">Generate Impact Brief (PDF)</div>
        <div class="dp-context-item">Compare with Active Framework</div>
        <div class="dp-context-sep"></div>
        <div class="dp-context-item danger">⚠ Flag for Emergency Review</div>
      </div>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Action</th><th>API call</th><th>Result</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>View Full Audit Trail</td><td><code>GET /api/v2/governance/audit_logs?country=&amp;proposal_id=</code></td><td>Dark-themed monospace modal of all events for that proposal</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Generate Impact Brief (PDF)</td><td><code>POST /api/v2/audit/reports/compliance {report_type: "impact_brief", proposal_id}</code></td><td>Returns <code>report_id</code>; confirmation dialog shown</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Compare with Active Framework</td><td>No API — uses cached <code>m_currentProposal</code></td><td>3-column table: Metric | Active Framework | Proposed Change; diff rows highlighted amber</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Flag for Emergency Review</td><td><code>POST /api/v2/governance/proposals/:id/flag {flag_type: "emergency_review"}</code></td><td>Escalates to top of queue for all board members; confirmation shown</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h4>Consensus Quorum / Voting Log Table</h4>
      <p>Right-clicking any row in <code>tblGovVotingLog</code> opens:</p>
      <div class="dp-context-menu">
        <div class="dp-context-item">Verify Cryptographic Signature</div>
        <div class="dp-context-item">View Member Credentials</div>
        <div class="dp-context-item">Inspect Vote Metadata</div>
        <div class="dp-context-sep"></div>
        <div class="dp-context-item">↻ Resend Quorum Notification</div>
      </div>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Action</th><th>API call / source</th><th>Result</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Verify Cryptographic Signature</td><td><code>POST /api/v2/audit/verify_signature {voter_id, proposal_id}</code></td><td>✅ VALID / ❌ INVALID + Key ID dialog</td></tr>
          <tr><td>View Member Credentials</td><td>Derived from <code>voter_cb_code</code> seat mapping</td><td>Dialog: Voter ID, canonical Key ID (CBK-KEY-01…EXT), auth level, timestamp, decision</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Inspect Vote Metadata</td><td>Constructed from row data + <code>m_currentProposal</code></td><td>Dark JSON pane (Courier New) showing raw vote object</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Resend Quorum Notification</td><td><code>POST /api/v2/governance/proposals/:id/notify {voter_id}</code></td><td>Disabled if member has already voted; confirmation on success</td></tr>
