    <%# ── §5 End-to-End User Flow ────────────────────────────────────────── %>
    <div class="dp-section" id="user-flow">
      <div class="dp-section-header">
        <div class="dp-section-num">§5</div>
        <h2>End-to-End User Interaction Flow</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="dp-flow">
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Draft Proposal</h4>
          <p>
            Authorized operator clicks <strong>+ New Proposal</strong>. Modal opens with
            fields for Category, Proposed Value, and Economic Impact Statement. The
            <code>effective_date</code> defaults to today + 14 days. On submit,
            <code>POST /api/v2/governance/proposals</code> creates the record with
            <code>status: pending</code>.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Proposal Appears in Queue</h4>
          <p>
            A new row appears in the Active Policy Briefs table with a human-readable
            reference (e.g. <code>GOV-2026-AF0C3B</code>), status <span class="s-pending">Pending</span>,
            and 0/3 quorum. Queue stats in the sidebar update. The Impact column in Corridor
            Caps shows "—" until the proposal is selected.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Board Review &amp; Impact Preview</h4>
          <p>
            Each board member selects the proposal. The left sidebar immediately runs the
            Delta-Check — affected corridor rows pulse amber and display the predicted
            ↑ / ↓ % change. The Policy Brief panel shows the Economic Impact Statement
            and Legal Reference. Members review the raw Policy JSON via the expandable
            dark code pane.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Voting — Multi-Sig Cast</h4>
          <p>
            Board members use the right-click menu on their seat row to verify their
            signature, then click <strong>🔒 Approve</strong>. High-risk proposals require
            PIN + typed APPROVE confirmation. Each vote is recorded via
            <code>POST /api/v2/governance/proposals/:id/vote {decision: "approve", voter_role}</code>.
            The board-seat chip for that member turns green. The quorum bar advances.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Quorum Threshold Met</h4>
          <p>
            Once <code>yes_votes / quorum_required ≥ 0.67</code>, the progress bar turns
            green, the Approve button becomes permanently active,
            <code>GovernanceQuorum.threshold_met_at</code> is recorded, and the Voting
            Status label changes to <em>"Quorum Reached — Executable"</em>. The API
            response includes <code>quorum_met: true</code> and <code>execution_ready: true</code>.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>DLT Anchoring — Immutable Seal</h4>
          <p>
            The lead administrator clicks <strong>Accrue Policy</strong>. The system
            SHA-256 hashes <code>policy_json</code>, posts to
            <code>POST /api/v2/governance/anchor {country, proposal_id, policy_hash}</code>,
            receives the DLT transaction ID, and writes it to <code>DLTAnchor</code>.
            The Immutable Seal badge appears green. Framework Status updates to
            <span class="s-active">Active</span> globally across the application.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Audit Trail &amp; Registry Update</h4>
          <p>
            The full lifecycle — proposed_by, submitted_at, each vote (voter_id, timestamp,
            decision, key_id), anchor_tx, anchored_at — is permanently recorded in the
            audit log. The Governance Queue removes the proposal from the active list
            (status → <code>executed</code>). The Audit &amp; Reports tab Registry Status
            reflects the change globally.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%# ── §6 Validation & System Effects ────────────────────────────────── %>
    <div class="dp-section" id="validation">
      <div class="dp-section-header">
        <div class="dp-section-num">§6</div>
        <h2>Validation &amp; System Effects</h2>
      </div>

      <h3>Suspension Block</h3>
      <div class="dp-lock-banner">
        ⛔ FRAMEWORK SUSPENDED — All write actions are locked. Policy anchoring is frozen until status is restored to Active.
      </div>
      <p>When <code>policy_status = SUSPENDED</code> (returned by the domains endpoint):</p>
      <ul style="padding-left:20px;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:2;">
        <li>The Constitution Status badge changes to red <strong>⛔ SUSPENDED</strong> with an <code>#ffebee</code> pill background.</li>
        <li>The Corridor Caps table receives a <code>2px solid #b71c1c</code> border and <code>#fff8f8</code> background.</li>
        <li>The <strong>🔒 Approve</strong> button is disabled with a tooltip: <em>"Framework is SUSPENDED — voting locked."</em></li>
        <li>The <strong>Accrue Policy / Immutable Seal</strong> button is disabled.</li>
        <li>All POST endpoints for <code>/vote</code>, <code>/anchor</code>, and <code>/execute</code> return <code>HTTP 423 Locked</code>.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Security Lock — HSM Key Policy</h3>
      <div class="dp-callout dp-danger">
        <span class="dp-ci">⛔</span>
        <div>
          No private keys are stored in the PostgreSQL database or transmitted over the API.
          All vote signing is handled externally via an HSM or secure vault. The
          <code>GovernanceVote.signature_key_id</code> field records only the key identifier
          (e.g. <code>CBK-KEY-01</code>), never the private key material.
          The Qt client calls the external HSM at vote-cast time; Rails only receives the
          signed payload and key reference.
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Self-Approval Block</h3>
      <div class="dp-callout dp-danger">
        <span class="dp-ci">⛔</span>
        <div>
          <code>POST /api/v2/governance/proposals/:id/vote</code> compares the Doorkeeper
          token identity of the voter against <code>GovernanceProposal.submitted_by</code>.
          If they match, the server returns <code>HTTP 403 Forbidden</code> with body
          <code>{ "error": "Self-approval not permitted" }</code>. The client shows a
          QMessageBox warning and does not update any UI state.
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>State Persistence on Restart</h3>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>State</th><th>Persisted?</th><th>Behaviour on restart</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Pending governance proposals</td><td class="r">YES</td><td>Fully reloaded from DB via <code>GET /api/v2/governance/proposals</code> on tab initialize</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Vote records</td><td class="r">YES</td><td>Votes are permanent; board-seat chips re-render from loaded votes array</td></tr>
          <tr><td>DLT Anchor records</td><td class="r">YES</td><td>Immutable — always present after anchoring; sync status re-fetched</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Active Preview (Validation Desk)</td><td class="r">NO</td><td>Cleared on restart; no session state persisted for in-progress validation views</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Selected proposal</td><td class="r">NO</td><td>Clears on restart; user must re-select from table</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Filter controls</td><td class="r">NO</td><td>Reset to defaults (All / All / empty dates) on restart</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>Status Transition Rules</h3>
      <div class="dp-rule">
        pending → open           (when quorum begins, first vote cast)<br>
        open    → approved       (when quorum_count / quorum_required ≥ 0.67)<br>
        open    → rejected       (when majority votes are "no")<br>
        approved → executed      (after DLT anchor succeeds; written via update_column to bypass enum)<br>
        pending | open → expired (when effective_date passes with no quorum)
      </div>

      <div class="dp-callout dp-info">
        <span class="dp-ci">ℹ</span>
        <div>
          The <code>executed</code> status is written via <code>update_column(:status, "executed")</code>
          to bypass the Rails enum validator, which does not include "executed" in the
          standard lifecycle enum definition. This is intentional — execution is a one-way
          terminal state that must succeed even if enum validation is tightened in future migrations.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%# ── §7 API Reference ───────────────────────────────────────────────── %>
    <div class="dp-section" id="api">
      <div class="dp-section-header">
        <div class="dp-section-num">§7</div>
        <h2>API Reference</h2>
      </div>

      <p>All endpoints are under the <code>/api/v2/</code> namespace. Request and response bodies are JSON. Authentication via Doorkeeper Bearer token. All write endpoints enforce the self-approval block and, when framework status is SUSPENDED, return <code>HTTP 423 Locked</code>.</p>

      <h3>Governance Proposals</h3>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Path</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>GET</td><td class="f">/api/v2/governance/proposals</td><td>List proposals. Accepts: <code>country</code>, <code>status</code>, <code>proposal_type</code>, <code>risk_level</code>, <code>submitted_by</code>, <code>proposal_id</code>, <code>date_from</code>, <code>date_to</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td>POST</td><td class="f">/api/v2/governance/proposals</td><td>Create proposal. Body: <code>{ proposal: { type, country, new_cap, effective_date, justification } }</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td>GET</td><td class="f">/api/v2/governance/proposals/:id</td><td>Single proposal with embedded <code>votes[]</code> array. Used to populate all three panes simultaneously.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>POST</td><td class="f">/api/v2/governance/proposals/:id/vote</td><td>Cast vote. Body: <code>{ decision: "approve"|"reject", voter_role }</code>. Returns <code>{ quorum_met, execution_ready, proposal_status }</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td>POST</td><td class="f">/api/v2/governance/proposals/:id/execute</td><td>Execute approved proposal. Triggers downstream system effects (cap updates, rate changes). Requires quorum already met.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>POST</td><td class="f">/api/v2/governance/proposals/:id/flag</td><td>Escalate to emergency review. Body: <code>{ flag_type: "emergency_review", country }</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td>POST</td><td class="f">/api/v2/governance/proposals/:id/notify</td><td>Resend quorum notification to a specific member. Body: <code>{ voter_id, country }</code></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>Domain &amp; Constitution</h3>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Path</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>GET</td><td class="f">/api/v2/governance/domains</td><td>Framework info for a jurisdiction. Params: <code>country</code>. Returns <code>active_framework</code>, <code>policy_status</code>, <code>monetary_authority</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td>GET</td><td class="f">/api/v2/governance/compliance</td><td>Constitution version and review date. Params: <code>country</code>. Returns <code>policy_name</code>, <code>limit_review_date</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td>GET</td><td class="f">/api/v2/governance/system_metrics</td><td>Monetary policy controls and corridor caps. Params: <code>country</code>. Returns <code>daily_issuance_cap</code>, <code>reserve_coverage_ratio</code>, <code>corridors[]</code></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>DLT Anchoring</h3>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Path</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>GET</td><td class="f">/api/v2/dlt/status</td><td>Node status, sync status, latest block, last anchor TX. Polled on tab initialize and after every anchor.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>POST</td><td class="f">/api/v2/governance/anchor</td><td>Anchor policy hash. Body: <code>{ country, proposal_id, policy_hash }</code>. Returns <code>{ dlt_anchor_tx, policy_hash }</code></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>Audit &amp; Reporting</h3>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Path</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>GET</td><td class="f">/api/v2/governance/audit_logs</td><td>Audit events for governance. Params: <code>country</code>, optional <code>proposal_id</code> to scope to a single proposal.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>POST</td><td class="f">/api/v2/audit/reports/compliance</td><td>Generate certified report. Body: <code>{ proposal_id, country, report_type: "impact_brief" }</code>. Returns <code>{ report_id }</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td>POST</td><td class="f">/api/v2/audit/verify_signature</td><td>Verify a board member's cryptographic signature for a vote. Body: <code>{ voter_id, proposal_id }</code>. Returns <code>{ valid, key_id }</code></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>Canonical API Envelope Format</h3>
      <p>All v2 governance endpoints return responses in the following envelope:</p>
      <div class="dp-json-block">
{<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="jk">"meta"</span>: {<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="jk">"api_version"</span>: <span class="jv">"v2"</span>,<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="jk">"request_id"</span>: <span class="jv">"req_abc123"</span>,<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="jk">"timestamp"</span>: <span class="jv">"2026-04-16T09:00:00Z"</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;},<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="jk">"data"</span>: { <span class="jv">/* payload */</span> },<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="jk">"error"</span>: <span class="jb">null</span><br>
}
      </div>
      <p>
        The Qt client reads <code>envelope["data"]</code> in all API callbacks. Errors are
        surfaced via <code>envelope["error"]</code> as a string; non-null error causes a
        <code>QMessageBox::warning</code> and aborts state updates.
      </p>
    </div>

